Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on characterizing large online social networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the optimization of sampling methods for NoSQL graph databases, which is related to software engineering. 
3. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper utilizes NoSQL graph databases and Web API for graph sampling, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
4. cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) - The paper deals with online social networks and their characterization, which is related to computational social science. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses sampling methods and their convergence guarantees, which is related to data structures and algorithms.
